See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: The New Zealand Medal (its correct name, not Maori War Medal) was awarded to those who had actually been under fire in any engagement from 1845 through 1847 or from 1860 through 1872. It was approved for award to British troops in 1869 and six months later extended to colonial forces.
