Quote: THE NEW ZEALAND (MAORI WAR) MEDAL. [heading] ... The Gazette issued at Auckland on 23 October, 1869, p. 590, notifies the extension to the Colonial Forces of the grant for the decoration conferred `for the War in New Zealand to all persons whether belonging to the local forces or loyal native tribes, who were actually under fire in any engagement with the enemy, or were otherwise conspicuous for distinguished service in the field.'
